#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&rkward; is meant to be(come) an easy to use graphical frontend to the "
"powerful &R; language for statistical computing. Since &R; is a full "
"featured programming language, &rkward; will never be able to offer a "
"complete GUI for everything in &R;. However, &rkward; strives to make common "
"task simple, to provide an easy entry point for newcomers, while at the same "
"time, transparent access to the full power of the underlying &R; language is "
"provided for advanced users."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &rkward;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most documentation is available from inside &rkward; itself by selecting "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Help</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> in &rkward; from the menu, <emphasis>not</emphasis> in this "
"document."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A useful guide to getting started with &rkward; is <ulink url=\"https://"
"rkward.kde.org/User_Documentation\">User Documentation Section in the "
"&rkward; wiki</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please go there for an introduction to &rkward;, and contact us, if you can "
"help with creating user documentation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Developer's Guide to &rkward;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
